Angelia: E, Everybody please listen to me... the Kingdom is tearing down the factory district because of the "Factory Renovation Project".
Angelia: The purpose of this project is to make everyone's lives better...
Hyacinthus: Nigel?
Nigel: Cin, what's with the crowd?
Hyacinthus: Someone from the Kingdom is here to tell us that they are rebuilding the factory district. That way we can get more job opportunities and better pay.
Hyacinthus: I don't really care; gotta get my hands on the food first~
Nigel: Who's that talking in front of the crowd?
Hyacinthus: I think it's someone from the Capitol. It's way too noisy, so I can't hear.
Angelia: During the renovation, we will establish distribution centers to distribute food to those who are temporarily unemployed.
Angelia: When the renovation is complete, everyone's job will...
Lucky: Look out; I already told you this place is dangerous. Escort the princess out of here!
Angelia: Wait, I'm not finished yet...
Hyacinthus: Nigel, it's Jim.
Jim: Give me your money! NOW!
Nigel: Cin, stay back!
Nigel: Cin, go back to the house.
Hyacinthus: What's up? I can help!
Nigel: Don't ask questions, just go back!
Nigel: He is acting so violently because of this stuff; just what on earth is this?
Eve: Is Jim...okay?
Nigel: He's fine.  By the way Eve, why did you come home so late?
Nigel: Where did you get these?
Eve: I stole them from the businessman who planned the renovation. I've been keeping an eye on him for a while now...
Nigel: Are these all real?
Eve: It seems...they are tearing down more than just the factory district.
Nigel: Impossible. If the residential area is part of the teardown, they won't promote it so openly. Plus, they said they will be distributing food to...
Eve: But, just look at all the extra areas they plan to tear down...
Nigel: A piece of paper proves nothing. Besides, if the renovation is successful, there will be more job opportunities.
Nigel: The children's lives will certainly improve!
Eve: This is no opportunity! They've done nothing except try to exploit us.
Eve: Have you forgotten how they treated us in the past and what they did to your mother...?
Nigel: What did you just say!
Eve: If that's the case, I'll protect this place with my own methods!
Nigel: Hey!
